-- Colombian Stocks: Helm Bank SA, El Condor, Bolsa de Valores
-- B y   A n d r e a   J a r a m i l l o
-- 2012-04-10T21:44:21Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-10/colombian-stocks-helm-bank-sa-el-condor-bolsa-de-valores.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Bogota trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of 3 p.m. local time.  The  IGBC Index (IGBC)  fell 0.2 percent to 14,864.86 while the
 Colcap Index (COLCAP)  declined 0.3 percent to 1,739.48.  Helm Bank SA (PFBHELM)  (PFBHELMB CB) reversed an earlier decline,
rising 0.4 percent to 462 pesos.  Helm Corp., the holding company of Helm Bank, hired
Inverlink SA to study options for its stake in the Colombian
lender, according to a regulatory filing today. The shares fell
as much as 7.8 percent today, the steepest intraday drop since
October 2008, after the lender in a separate statement denied a
report that a controlling stake in the company has been sold.  Construcciones El Condor SA (ELCONDOR)  (ELCONDOR CB), a Colombian
construction company specializing in infrastructure projects,
traded at 1,360 pesos in its debut, 3.9 percent less than the
1,415 pesos at which the shares were sold in an initial public
offering last month.  Bolsa de Valores de Colombia SA  (BVC CB), the operator of
 Colombia â€™s main stock exchange, fell 0.3 percent to 33.5 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
